node.text:
The new litter 😔

A seahorse clings to a face mask – By photographer Nicholas Samaras.

This heart-breaking image is one of the finalists for the Ocean Photography Awards, which has a simple mission: to shine a light on the beauty of the ocean and also the threats it faces.
​
Image credit: @nicholas_samaras @ocean_photography_awards
#nature #waste #recycle

node.text:
This baby chimp was born with broken ribs, had pneumonia, and was abandoned by his own mother.

A human couple raised him and showed him love.

Today — this is how he reacts whenever he sees them…

(Vid via @limbanizwf Caption via @notrexchapman) #animals #rescue #heartwarming

node.text:
Have you ever seen amphibian eggs? 👀 ⁣
⁣
While it's never a good idea to mess with nature, I'm happy to report that these eggs were carefully put back in the water to continue growing. ⁣
⁣
These are believed to be from some species of frog, but pretty much all amphibian eggs are this way. ⁣
⁣
They lay their eggs in jelly-like masses which are then kept in water to avoid drying up (if they dry up they die). ⁣
⁣
The jelly protects them from predators and also helps to attract warmth to the eggs from the sun. ⁣
⁣
🎥: @justinnterryy
